@keveman - this seems to be tf.layers loading a custom bucketization_op via `load_op_library` for the second time.
The dynamic loader presumably returns a status indicating the shared library is already loaded - but this causes TF to fail rather then use the existing version.
(Obviously this is an unanticipated use case!)
